<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13459] A more robust Verify Replication </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13459</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have done quite a bit of data center migration work in the past year.  We modified verify replication a bit to help us out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Things like:&lt;br/&gt;
Ignoring timestamps when comparing Cells&lt;br/&gt;
More detailed counters when discrepancies are reported between rows added the following counters: &lt;br/&gt;
SOURCEMISSINGROWS,TARGETMISSINGROWS,SOURCEMISSINGKEYS, TARGETMISSINGKEYS&lt;br/&gt;
Also added the ability to run this job on any pair of tables and clusters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If folks are interested I can put up the patch and backport.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
